CC  The decarboxylation of L-ornithine to putrescine consumes a proton.
CC  Exchange of putrescine for L-ornithine by an antiporter completes a
CC  cycle that effectively removes a cytosolic protein.
CC  Decarboxylation/antiporter systems for this and other (e.g.
CC  aspartate-alanine) substrate pairs can provide protection against
CC  acidic pH.
